  "bench_knowledge": [
    "High-viscosity non-protein liquids (e.g., pure glycerol, PEG solutions) resist aspiration, causing back-pressure that stalls the piston and under-delivers volume. Wide-bore tips reduce hydraulic resistance. Reverse pipetting removes the dead-air step. A 2\u20133 s post-aspirate pause lets the meniscus stabilise before withdrawal.",
    "Surfactants above their CMC form micelles that stabilise foam. Any air-liquid interface created by dispensing rapidly or by blowout air bubbles generates persistent foam. Dispensing slowly along the tube wall prevents air entrainment. Touch-off tip on the wall instead of final blowout eliminates the last drop of air."
  ],
